		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=54971#54971" class="postlink">Concentration Camp</a> looks great for a NES game, the animations are very smooth and the cards are pretty colorful. I guess you can go crazy with the colors, since only 2 cards are visible at a time and you can probably reconfigure their palettes every time they are flipped.
<br />
<br />But I have to admit I'm a little disappointed though. When you said you were working on something new I expected something more action-oriented, with scrolling and moving objects, specially since you were working on President and all, but no, it's just yet another 1-screen puzzle game.

		

